tests shouldn't add reflect-config for a library unless it's absolutely necessary, since the dynamic agent is responsible for generating the actual metadata. I wonder about finding the right balance in handling metadata to optimize testing without unnecessary complications. It's a bit of a tricky situation, but I'm determined to clarify it!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering library behavior**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking at the behavior of the library, and it includes ResolverConfig, which might help with missing elements. However, the active dynamic-access report from JVM isn't native. I don't want to fix the native part. I'm wondering if adding reflect-config is necessary. The resource bundle may also mask test metadata, but since the resource isn’t in the library and is only for tests, it seems fine to have resource-config under \\\\\\\"tests-only.\\\\\\\" I'll just add resource-config.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_59zOCqg82vPvqrdE9waPE5l2|fc_0ee368ff6ff029c80169f4dbac26a0819cac138c18ace4a776\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/dnsjava-tests-only/resource-config.json\", \"content\": \"{\\n  \\\"resources\\\": {\\n    \\\"includes\\\": [\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"bundles\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"org.xbill.DNS.windows.DNSServer\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 417, \"output\": 712, \"cacheRead\": 41984, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 43113, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777654688769, \"responseId\": \"resp_0ee368ff6ff029c80169f4dba15154819cacb8283a9ddd4274\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-58-50-673024Z.log:23360:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_e